President Cyril Ramaphosa has commended the country’s nine premiers for ensuring that integrated development in their provinces benefits rural areas. He was speaking at the opening of the President’s Coordinating Council at the Union Buildings in Pretoria on Friday morning. The meeting was called to receive progress report on the implementation of the government’s district-based model for development. The model is meant to improve service delivery in a coordinated manner across all three spheres of government. Ramaphosa says the model is beginning to bear fruit. In the video below, President Ramaphosa chairs the 2nd President’s Coordinating Council meeting  President Ramaphosa launched the model’s three pilot projects in the rural setting of OR Tambo District in the Eastern Cape, followed by the metropolitan City of eThekwini in KwaZulu-Natal and then at the mining region of Waterberg District Municipality in Limpopo. In the video below, President Ramaphosa launches the District Development Model:   